{<b>Exercise One Answers</b>

<b><i>1-1</i></b><i> and <b>1-5</b> are 2/1 GF auctions.</i>

<b><i>1-2</i></b><i> is a jump shift to the two-level and is unaffected by 2/1 GF.</i>

<b><i>1-3</i></b><i> and <b>1-4</b> have interference. The 2/1 responses are forcing, but not to game.</i>

<b><i>1-6</i></b><i> is a raise, not a new suit response.</i>}
[BCFlags "2000017"]

